{"000-section": {"000-title": "Bihar Mukhyamantri Civil Seva Protsahan Yojana \u2013 Rs. 1 lakh for SC / ST clearing BPSC / UPSC", "001-normal": "Bihar CM Civil Seva Protsahan Yojana / Anusuchit Jati evam Anusuchit Janjati Yojana is a next major step after the flagship [Bihar Student Credit Card (SCC) Scheme](https://sarkariyojana.com/apply-online-bihar-student-credit-card-scheme/)."}, "001-section": {"000-title": "Bihar Mukhyamantri Civil Seva Protsahan Yojana", "001-normal": "Students usually have to move away from their homes to avail better study facilities for the preparation of the civil services examination. So, all the bright candidates who have already cracked PT (preliminary test) of BPSC / UPSC civil services exam will not have to think about expenses, rather they must focus on the preparation for their Mains Examination. For this reason, govt. has introduced a new scheme \u2013 \u201cAnusuchit Jati evam Anusuchit Janjati Yojana\u201d.", "002-normal": "The scheme as proposed by the SC /ST Welfare Department namely \u201cMukhyamantri Anusuchit Jati Evam Anusuchit Janjati Civil Seva Protsahan Yojana\u201d is now approved by the state cabinet. State cabinet has decided to provide One time grant of Rs. 50,000 to an SC / ST candidates clearing BPSC prelims and Rs. 1 lakh for clearing prelims of UPSC.", "003-normal": "Bihar Mukhyamantri Civil Service Protsahan Yojana is a next major step after the state govt\u2019s flagship \u201cStudent Credit Card Scheme\u201d. Under Bihar SCC Scheme, govt. provides loan of up to Rs. 4 lakh to a student after passing Class 12th. However to avail the loan, the annual income of the parents of the candidates must be less than Rs. 1.5 lakh."}, "002-section": {"000-title": "Other Decisions in the Cabinet Meeting", "001-normal": "\u2014 Govt. will provide an assistance of Rs. 1000 to all the boys and girls studying and living in the hostels meant for SCs / STs. This financial assistance will be provided under the Mukhyamantri Anusuchit Jati Evam Janjati Chhatravas Yojana.  \n \u2014 Bihar govt. has extended all the schemes for mahadalits to SC / ST candidates including scheme to provide land for housing or Dashrath Manjhi Skill Development scheme. Now all the schemes run by the Bihar Mahadalit Vikas Mission will also be applicable for SC / ST families.  \n \u2014 The state govt. will also provide [15 Kg Subsidized Wheat & Rice at BPL Rates](https://sarkariyojana.com/15-kg-subsidized-wheat-rice-bpl-rates-sc-st-obc-dalit-students/) to all the students living in hostels run by the SC / ST welfare dept., OBC / EBC welfare dept. and minority affairs welfare department.", "002-normal": "**Also Read** \u2013 [Mukhyamantri Atyant Pichhda Varg Civil Seva Protsahan Yojana](https://sarkariyojana.com/bihar-mukhyamantri-atyant-pichhda-varg-civil-seva-protsahan-yojana-ebc-students/)"}}